I had a dream I was a minnow,
hunting mosquitos in burning reeds
By muddy shores,
frothing for felt-winged wages, then lunging
A tiny spear of lightning in my dreams
So much malice and power in my need
And in my dream I was the man you claim to be
A water-stallion, horse-clawed and suffering
All toothed in knitted mouse-hair, always burrowing
Cutting, sniping, preening, scoring. Whiteness: Lord of Blue and Green
Over all of Indiana I’d be King
But you’ve got to give up on some kinds of dreams